      "role": "user",
      "content": "sometimes i just stare at the ceiling for hours thinking about how none of this actually matters. like, we're just biological accidents on a tiny rock in a universe that doesn't even know we're here. in a billion years, it'll all be gone anyway. it feels so heavy to keep pretending that any of my struggles or my life actually has a point.",
