    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that \"meaning\" feels so manufactured, you know? like we're just patching up a sinking ship with duct tape to distract ourselves from the fact that the ocean is infinite and we're doomed. if nothing matters on a cosmic scale, then all this effort—working, loving, trying to survive—it just feels like a cruel joke. why put in the effort to keep the ship afloat if the destination is just more emptiness?",
